## `extract_cons` family

List-only (no Array counterpart — `cons` is List-specific).

```lean src/Init/Data/List/Extract.lean:/^theorem extract_cons_of_start_pos/../^$/
  simp [takeWhile_eq_take_findIdx_not, extract_eq_drop_take']

===
theorem extract_cons_of_start_pos (h : 0 < i) :
    (a :: as).extract i j = as.extract (i - 1) (j - 1) := by
  apply ext_getElem
  · simp; omega
  · intro p h₁ h₂
    have : i + p ≠ 0 := by omega
    simp only [getElem_extract, getElem_cons, reduceDIte, *]
    congr 1; omega
===

theorem extract_cons_zero_of_stop_pos (h : 0 < j) :
```

```lean src/Init/Data/List/Extract.lean:/^theorem extract_cons_zero_of_stop_pos/../^$/
    congr 1; omega

===
theorem extract_cons_zero_of_stop_pos (h : 0 < j) :
    (a :: as).extract 0 j = a :: as.extract 0 (j - 1) := by
  apply ext_getElem
  · simp; omega
  · intro p h₁ h₂
    simp only [getElem_extract, Nat.zero_add, getElem_cons]
===

theorem extract_cons :
```

```lean src/Init/Data/List/Extract.lean:/^theorem extract_cons :/../^end List/
    simp only [getElem_extract, Nat.zero_add, getElem_cons]

===
theorem extract_cons :
    (a :: as).extract i j =
      if 0 < i ∨ j = 0 then as.extract (i - 1) (j - 1) else a :: as.extract (i - 1) (j - 1) := by
  split <;> rename_i h
  · cases h
    · exact extract_cons_of_start_pos ‹_›
    · simp [*]
  · simp only [not_or, Nat.not_lt, Nat.le_zero_eq, Nat.ne_zero_iff_zero_lt] at h
    simp +contextual [extract_cons_zero_of_stop_pos, *]

===
end List
```

## Summary of remaining inconsistencies

1. **`extract_set` structure**: Array has 3 branches (k < i, k < min j size, else) with explicit `(h : k < as.size)`. List has 2 branches (k < i, else) without the hypothesis. The List version doesn't distinguish the case where `k ≥ j` (where `set` is a no-op on the extract).
2. **`set_extract` hypothesis**: Array requires `(h : k < (as.extract i j).size)`. List has no such hypothesis (List.set is total).
3. **`extract_succ_right`**: Array uses `.push as[j]`, List uses `++ [as[j]]` — inherent type difference.
4. **`extract_sub_one`**: Array uses `.pop`, List uses `.dropLast` — inherent type difference.
5. **Missing List equivalents**: `extract_push`/`extract_push_of_le` (concat analogue), `extract_eq_pop` (dropLast analogue), `push_extract_getElem`.
6. **`getElem?_extract_of_lt_stop`**: List-only variant; Array only has the stronger `getElem?_extract_of_lt` (with `k < min j as.size - i`).
